The article discusses the importance of healthcare as a right for all Americans. It highlights that the open enrollment period on HealthCare.gov has begun, allowing people to obtain quality and affordable health coverage until January 15th, 2024. Last year, over 16 million people signed up for health insurance through the Affordable Care Act, with coverage on HealthCare.gov and state-based Marketplaces becoming more accessible and affordable. The Inflation Reduction Act has helped lower premiums, with consumers saving an average of $800 annually. The article encourages individuals without employer-provided insurance to explore the various affordable coverage options available to them. The author urges readers to visit HealthCare.gov to renew their coverage or find a suitable plan.